Body and Design

column1:
Nothing beats the icy cool calmness of stainless steel and the Fossil watch exemplifies the timeless appeal of this metal. The soft-toned round dial that measures 37 mm in diameter has bold time markers and three time display hands and the dial is surrounded by a minute marker bezel. The dial sits within a 10 mm thick stainless steel case that is tough and scratch-resistant. So if you are reaching behind the couch to get your little one’s toys and accidentally graze the watch against the wall you don’t have to worry about scratching. To hold the timepiece on your wrist is the lovely 18 mm wide stainless steel strap. The brushed and polished finish of the bracelet type strap truly adds to the regal appeal of the watch.

Features and Other Functions

A sturdy watch makes a lot of sense in the life of a busy woman. The Fossil watch pairs beauty with functionality by featuring the useful date and day display function on the watch. The watch also comes with water resistance of up to a depth of 50 m. So if you decide to join your friends in the pool you dive right in with your watch on.
The Fossil analog watch is not just an accessory it is a definition of the kind of woman you are - strong
